AstaroGuard Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 3/24/26
About This Policy

Your privacy is important to us. It is AstaroGuard's policy to respect your privacy and comply with applicable United States laws and regulations regarding any personal information we may collect about you.

Personal information is any information about you that can be used to identify you. This includes information such as your name, email address, device information, payment details, and information about how you interact with our website or services.

Information we collect falls into one of two categories:

Voluntarily Provided Information
Automatically Collected Information

“Voluntarily provided” information refers to information you knowingly provide to us when using our services or contacting us.

Logged Data

We do not collect, store, or obtain user public or private data unless otherwise stated.

Personal Information

We will never request personal information unless you are contacting us regarding an issue or support request.

Examples include:

Email addresses when contacting support.
Legitimate Reasons for Processing Personal Information

We only collect and use personal information when we have a legitimate business purpose to do so. In such cases, we only collect personal information that is reasonably necessary to provide our services.

Use of Data

We may collect personal information when you:

Contact us via email or social media
Communicate with our support team

We may use this information for purposes including:

Providing our platform's services
Responding to inquiries
Security and fraud prevention
Maintaining safe and reliable services

We may combine voluntarily provided information with general research or analytical data to improve our services and user experience.

Security of Your Personal Information

We take commercially reasonable measures to protect your personal information from:

Loss
Theft
Unauthorized access
Disclosure
Modification

However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute data security.

You are responsible for maintaining the security of any credentials you use with our services.

How Long We Keep Personal Information

We retain personal information only as long as necessary to fulfill the purpose for which it was collected.

For example:

Support emails may be retained while a support request remains open.
Records may be retained for legal, accounting, or compliance obligations.

When information is no longer required, we delete or anonymize it.

Disclosure of Personal Information to Third Parties

We may disclose personal information to:

Employees or contractors working with AstaroGuard
Service providers (hosting, IT services, analytics, etc.)
Payment processors
Professional advisors
Law enforcement or regulatory authorities when required by law
Entities involved in a business merger or acquisition

Third-party providers we currently use include:

Render
Azure
Children's Privacy

Our services are not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 in compliance with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).

If we become aware that we have collected such data, we will delete it promptly.

International Data Transfers

Information we collect may be stored or processed in the United States or other countries where our service providers operate.

If information is transferred internationally, we will take reasonable measures to ensure it is protected according to this privacy policy and applicable laws.

Your Rights and Control Over Your Information

You have the right to:

Request access to personal data we hold about you
Request corrections to inaccurate data
Request deletion of your data where applicable
Opt-out of marketing communications
Request information about how your data is used

Requests can be submitted by contacting us.

Business Transfers

If AstaroGuard or its assets are acquired or merged with another company, user data may be transferred as part of the business assets. The acquiring entity will be required to follow this privacy policy.

Limits of Our Policy

Our services may link to third-party websites or platforms. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those third parties.

Changes to This Policy

We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in:

Business practices
Legal requirements
Technology or services

Updates will be posted on this page.

U.S. State Privacy Law Compliance

This policy complies with applicable U.S. state privacy laws including:

California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
California Privacy Rights Act (CPRA)
Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA)
Colorado Privacy Act (CPA)
Utah Consumer Privacy Act (UCPA)
Florida Digital Bill of Rights

Residents of these states may have additional rights, including:

Right to know what personal data is collected
Right to request deletion
Right to opt-out of data sales or targeted advertising
Right to non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights

To exercise these rights, contact us using the information below.

Do Not Track

